<h2>Scope of this notice</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy is intended to describe DevAndDev's privacy practices and provide information about the choices
  you have regarding the ways in which information collected by DevAndDev is used and disclosed. </p>
<h2>Our commitment to privacy</h2>
<p>DevAndDev values your privacy. To better protect your privacy, we have provided this Policy explaining our
  information practices and the choices you can make about the way your personal information is collected, used and
  disclosed. </p>
<h2>The information we collect</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy applies to all information collected by or submitted to DevAndDev, including personal data.
  "Personal data" is data that can be used to identify an individual. </p>
<p>DevAndDev collects personal data when: </p>
<ul>
  <li>you create a user account;</li>
  <li>you change your profile settings;</li>
</ul>
<p> The types of personal data collected may include (but are not limited to): </p>
<ul>
  <li>your username</li>
  <li>your e-mail address;</li>
  <li>any information that DevAndDev collects online from you and maintains in association with your account, such as:
    <ul>
      <li>your system password,</li>
      <li>your IP address,</li>
      <li>your language preference,</li>
      <li>your timezone,</li>
      <li>your programming skills and level,</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>Publicly available personal data</h2>
<p>Some personal data attached to DevAndDev accounts is made public. Specifically: </p>
<ul>
  <li>your location (if defined),</li>
  <li>your timezone (if defined),</li>
  <li>your website, blog, or other affiliations (if defined).</li>
  <li>your programming skills and level,</li>
</ul>
<p>If you wish for this information to be kept private, you can remove this information from your account profile.
</p>
<h2>Using (processing) your personal data</h2>
<p>DevAndDev uses the personal data you provide to: </p>
<ul>
  <li>create and maintain your accounts;</li>
  <li>identify and authenticate you;</li>
  <li>answer your questions;</li>
  <li>send you information;</li>
</ul>
<h2>Sharing your personal data</h2>
<p>Unless you consent, DevAndDev will never process or share the personal data you provide to us except as described
  below. </p>
<p>DevAndDev may share your personal data with third parties under any of the following circumstances: </p>
<ul>
  <li>Your publicly available personal data in the DevAndDev account system, as described above, is accessible by anyone
  </li>
  <li>As required by law (such as responding to a valid subpoena, warrant, audit, or agency action, or to prevent
    fraud).</li>
  <li>For research activities, including the production of statistical reports (such aggregated information is used to
    describe our services and is not used to contact the subjects of the report).</li>
</ul>
<h2>Receiving e-mail</h2>
<p>DevAndDev may send you e-mail about your account, to communicate with you about your accounts, or in response to your
  questions. For your protection, DevAndDev may contact you in the event that we find an issue that requires your
  immediate attention. DevAndDev processes your personal data in these cases to fulfill and comply with its contractual
  obligations to you, to provide the services you have requested, and to ensure the security of your account. </p>
<h2>Cookies and other browser information </h2>
<p>DevAndDev's online services automatically capture IP addresses. We use IP addresses to help diagnose problems with
  our servers, to administer our website, and to help ensure the security of your interaction with our services. </p>
<p>As part of offering and providing customizable and personalized services, DevAndDev uses cookies to store and
  sometimes track information about you. A cookie is a small amount of data that is sent to your browser from a Web
  server and stored on your computer's hard drive. All sections of devand.dev where you are prompted to log in or
  that are customizable require your browser to accept cookies. </p>
<p>Generally, we use cookies to: </p>
<ol>
  <li>Remind us of who you are and to access your account information (stored on our computers) in order to provide a
    better and more personalized service. This cookie is set when you register or "sign in" and is removed when you
    "sign out" of our services.</li>
  <li>Keep valid form data, provide errors about invalid form data, generate captcha test against automated spam during "Sign up" process</li>
</ol>
<p>If you do not want your personal information to be stored by cookies, you can configure your browser so that it
  always rejects these cookies or asks you each time if you accept them or not. However, you must understand that the
  use of cookies may be necessary to provide certain services (see 1. above), and choosing to reject cookies will reduce
  the performance and functionality of the site. Your browser documentation includes instructions explaining how to
  enable, disable or delete cookies at the browser level (usually located in the “Help”, “Tools” or “Edit” facility).
</p>
<h2>Our commitment to data security</h2>
<p>DevAndDev staff and administrators are familiar with our privacy policy guidelines. Our websites enforce Transport
  Layer Security (TLS) connections, which encrypts your personal data when you send your personal information on our
  website. </p>
<h2>About links to other sites</h2>
<p>This site contains links to other sites. DevAndDev does not control the information collection of sites that can be
  reached through links from devand.dev site. If you have questions about the data collection procedures of linked
  sites, please contact those sites directly. </p>
<h2>Your rights under GDPR in the EEA</h2>
<p>Where the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text"
    href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/HTML/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679&amp;from=EN">EU General Data
    Protection Regulation</a>
  2016/679 (“GDPR”) applies to the processing of your personal data, especially when you access the website from a
  country in the European Economic Area (“EEA”), you have the following rights, subject to some limitations, against
  DevAndDev:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The right to access your personal data;</li>
  <li>The right to
    rectify the personal data we hold about you;</li>
  <li>The right to erase
    your personal data;</li>
  <li>The right to restrict our use of your personal
    data;</li>
  <li>The right to object to our use of your personal data;</li>
  <li>The right to receive your personal data in a usable electronic format and
    transmit it to a third party (also known as the right of data portability);
    and</li>
  <li>The right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection
    authority.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you would like to exercise any of these rights, please contact the administrators of the site. Please understand,
  however, the rights enumerated above are not absolute in all cases.
</p>
<p>Where the GDPR applies, you also have the right to withdraw any consent you have given to uses of your personal data.
  If you wish to withdraw consent that you have previously provided to DevAndDev, you may do so via email to the
  relevant administrators. However, the withdrawal of consent will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on
  consent before its withdrawal. </p>
<h2>How to access, modify or update your information</h2>
<p>DevAndDev gives you the ability to access, modify or update your personal data at any time. You may log in and make
  changes to your login information (change your password), your contact information, your general preferences and your
  personalization settings. If necessary, you may also contact us and describe the changes you want made to the personal
  data you have previously provided via email. </p>
<p>If you wish to remove your personal data from DevAndDev, you may contact us via email and request that we remove this
  information from the relevant DevAndDev Account System.</p>
<h2>How to contact us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about any of these practices or DevAndDev's use of
  your personal information, please feel free to contact us at <a rel="nofollow" class="external text"
    href="mailto:privacy@devand.dev">privacy@devand.dev</a>, and we will work with you to resolve any concerns you may
  have about this Policy. </p>
<h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>DevAndDev reserves the right to change this policy from time to time. If we do make changes, the revised Privacy
  Policy will be posted on this site.</p>
